WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:04.990 align:middle line:90%


00:00:04.990 --> 00:00:07.485 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:00:07.485 --> 00:00:20.542 align:middle line:90%


00:00:20.542 --> 00:00:23.000 align:middle line:10%
>> REGINA MEREDITH: It has not
been lost on any of you that

00:00:23.000 --> 00:00:25.820 align:middle line:10%
are human behavior is having
a negative impact on our host,

00:00:25.820 --> 00:00:26.930 align:middle line:10%
Mother Earth.

00:00:26.930 --> 00:00:30.410 align:middle line:10%
Martin Ogle, a naturalist with
a degree in wildlife sciences,

00:00:30.410 --> 00:00:33.350 align:middle line:10%
is our guest today, and we'll
be discussing the incredibly

00:00:33.350 --> 00:00:37.250 align:middle line:10%
intricate dance that occurs
between Earth's mind and ours

00:00:37.250 --> 00:00:40.400 align:middle line:10%
and what happens when we forget
that we're part of a whole.

00:00:40.400 --> 00:00:41.420 align:middle line:90%
Welcome, Martin.

00:00:41.420 --> 00:00:41.820 align:middle line:90%
>> MARTIN OGLE: Thank you.

00:00:41.820 --> 00:00:42.500 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: It's good
to have you here.

00:00:42.500 --> 00:00:44.330 align:middle line:84%
This is a really
important topic I

00:00:44.330 --> 00:00:46.932 align:middle line:84%
mean, we read the headlines
and everyone just goes,

00:00:46.932 --> 00:00:49.350 align:middle line:90%
ah, what are we going to do?

00:00:49.350 --> 00:00:52.200 align:middle line:84%
And then we hear all
the reports coming out.

00:00:52.200 --> 00:00:54.530 align:middle line:84%
We've reached that
tipping point.

00:00:54.530 --> 00:00:56.770 align:middle line:84%
The next extinction
is on its way.

00:00:56.770 --> 00:01:00.090 align:middle line:84%
And people, like the wonderful
people watching this show,

00:01:00.090 --> 00:01:03.530 align:middle line:84%
who care about such
things feel hopeless,

00:01:03.530 --> 00:01:05.160 align:middle line:84%
like there's nothing
more we can do.

00:01:05.160 --> 00:01:06.535 align:middle line:84%
There's nothing
that can be done.

00:01:06.535 --> 00:01:09.272 align:middle line:84%
No amount of intervention
is going to save us now.

00:01:09.272 --> 00:01:11.480 align:middle line:84%
And that's what the evening
headlines would indicate,

00:01:11.480 --> 00:01:13.400 align:middle line:84%
on one hand, and then
on the other hand,

00:01:13.400 --> 00:01:15.192 align:middle line:84%
depending on which
station you're watching,

00:01:15.192 --> 00:01:16.608 align:middle line:84%
eh, there's nothing
wrong, there's

00:01:16.608 --> 00:01:18.080 align:middle line:90%
no such thing as climate change.

00:01:18.080 --> 00:01:19.880 align:middle line:84%
So here, we're
having, hopefully,

00:01:19.880 --> 00:01:24.200 align:middle line:84%
a very wise and grounded
and calming discussion

00:01:24.200 --> 00:01:26.840 align:middle line:90%
about our need for maturity.

00:01:26.840 --> 00:01:27.640 align:middle line:90%
>> OGLE: Hope so.

00:01:27.640 --> 00:01:28.520 align:middle line:90%
>> REGINA: Yeah.

00:01:28.520 --> 00:01:31.760 align:middle line:84%
So first of all, I want to
talk about you as a little kid.

00:01:31.760 --> 00:01:33.830 align:middle line:84%
You led a different kind
of life than most people

00:01:33.830 --> 00:01:36.990 align:middle line:84%
watching who were born and
raised in the Western world.

00:01:36.990 --> 00:01:37.790 align:middle line:90%
You weren't.

00:01:37.790 --> 00:01:39.980 align:middle line:84%
And so tell us
about your childhood

00:01:39.980 --> 00:01:43.820 align:middle line:84%
and how you ended up being
raised for a number of years

00:01:43.820 --> 00:01:45.060 align:middle line:90%
in South Korea.

00:01:45.060 --> 00:01:45.860 align:middle line:90%
>> OGLE: Yeah.

00:01:45.860 --> 00:01:48.650 align:middle line:84%
Well, I was born there and
lived 10 of my first 14

00:01:48.650 --> 00:01:50.600 align:middle line:90%
years in South Korea.

00:01:50.600 --> 00:01:53.690 align:middle line:10%
My father was a
Methodist missionary,

00:01:53.690 --> 00:01:59.390 align:middle line:10%
and the work that he did was
largely industrial relations,

00:01:59.390 --> 00:02:02.120 align:middle line:10%
work in steel mills
and coal mines

00:02:02.120 --> 00:02:06.600 align:middle line:10%
and trying to get labor
rights for workers.

00:02:06.600 --> 00:02:09.330 align:middle line:10%
That was why he went
there or how he got there.

00:02:09.330 --> 00:02:11.090 align:middle line:10%
So I was born there
and lived there

00:02:11.090 --> 00:02:14.930 align:middle line:10%
and lived a, now I realize,
quite different life than most

00:02:14.930 --> 00:02:15.762 align:middle line:10%
people here.

00:02:15.762 --> 00:02:17.720 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: So let's talk
about the differences,

00:02:17.720 --> 00:02:20.690 align:middle line:84%
because this shaped who you are,
about what it was like being

00:02:20.690 --> 00:02:23.660 align:middle line:84%
raised in the East where you
have this, what seems to be,

00:02:23.660 --> 00:02:26.023 align:middle line:84%
kind of very dramatic
and even harsher climate

00:02:26.023 --> 00:02:27.440 align:middle line:84%
and environment,
in a certain way,

00:02:27.440 --> 00:02:30.440 align:middle line:84%
with these mountains and so
forth that you were playing

00:02:30.440 --> 00:02:31.490 align:middle line:90%
in as a kid.

00:02:31.490 --> 00:02:33.020 align:middle line:84%
Let's talk about
life in the East

00:02:33.020 --> 00:02:34.520 align:middle line:84%
and life in that
environment and how

00:02:34.520 --> 00:02:38.150 align:middle line:84%
you started really connecting
with this notion of time

00:02:38.150 --> 00:02:39.590 align:middle line:90%
and Earth.

00:02:39.590 --> 00:02:41.660 align:middle line:84%
>> OGLE: Korea is a very
mountainous country.

00:02:41.660 --> 00:02:45.030 align:middle line:84%
Otherwise and similarly,
it's very much like Virginia,

00:02:45.030 --> 00:02:48.290 align:middle line:84%
where I lived much of my life,
in climate and topography

00:02:48.290 --> 00:02:49.140 align:middle line:90%
and everything.

00:02:49.140 --> 00:02:51.920 align:middle line:84%
It is very highly
populated, however,

00:02:51.920 --> 00:02:55.160 align:middle line:84%
and so I grew up in a very
crowded, dense environment,

00:02:55.160 --> 00:02:59.390 align:middle line:84%
and I was pretty much
the only Caucasian child

00:02:59.390 --> 00:03:02.000 align:middle line:84%
to be found other
than my sisters.

00:03:02.000 --> 00:03:06.540 align:middle line:84%
And that kind of, obviously,
set a tone for my life.

00:03:06.540 --> 00:03:09.020 align:middle line:84%
But one of the things
that I really loved to do

00:03:09.020 --> 00:03:11.060 align:middle line:84%
was to go up in the
mountains and go mountain

00:03:11.060 --> 00:03:13.560 align:middle line:84%
climbing with my
father or whoever else.

00:03:13.560 --> 00:03:17.990 align:middle line:84%
And that obviously set
a very meaningful part

00:03:17.990 --> 00:03:21.200 align:middle line:84%
of my young existence that got
me into the kinds of things

00:03:21.200 --> 00:03:22.700 align:middle line:90%
that I love to do now.

00:03:22.700 --> 00:03:25.820 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: Was being in nature
or a part of nature part

00:03:25.820 --> 00:03:29.210 align:middle line:84%
of the Eastern
culture at that time?

00:03:29.210 --> 00:03:31.190 align:middle line:90%
>> OGLE: Yeah, I think so.

00:03:31.190 --> 00:03:35.540 align:middle line:84%
At that time, of course, Korea
was only about 15 years out

00:03:35.540 --> 00:03:39.770 align:middle line:84%
of the war when I was first
to third, fourth grade.

00:03:39.770 --> 00:03:43.440 align:middle line:84%
And it was a very
decimated landscape.

00:03:43.440 --> 00:03:46.790 align:middle line:84%
And so it was a different
thing kind of going out,

00:03:46.790 --> 00:03:48.500 align:middle line:90%
quote, unquote, "into nature."

00:03:48.500 --> 00:03:52.650 align:middle line:84%
But then and even now, people
love to go mountain climbing.

00:03:52.650 --> 00:03:54.260 align:middle line:84%
You'll go anywhere,
even in Seoul,

00:03:54.260 --> 00:03:56.760 align:middle line:84%
and some of the mountains that
are right in and around Seoul

00:03:56.760 --> 00:03:59.090 align:middle line:84%
always have people
all over them.

00:03:59.090 --> 00:04:01.483 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: Many years ago,
probably when you were--

00:04:01.483 --> 00:04:03.150 align:middle line:84%
because you're a
little younger than me,

00:04:03.150 --> 00:04:04.760 align:middle line:84%
so probably when you
were a kid there,

00:04:04.760 --> 00:04:07.365 align:middle line:84%
I would fly in and out because
I worked with an airline,

00:04:07.365 --> 00:04:09.740 align:middle line:84%
World Airways, who was flying
troops in and out of Seoul,

00:04:09.740 --> 00:04:10.550 align:middle line:90%
right?

00:04:10.550 --> 00:04:12.170 align:middle line:90%
And I remember the landscape.

00:04:12.170 --> 00:04:13.940 align:middle line:90%
I was there in the winter.

00:04:13.940 --> 00:04:16.430 align:middle line:84%
And I remember the
landscape at the time

00:04:16.430 --> 00:04:19.709 align:middle line:84%
and thinking how stark it
was from my point of view,

00:04:19.709 --> 00:04:22.730 align:middle line:84%
but now we're probably coming
in through military base is

00:04:22.730 --> 00:04:24.830 align:middle line:90%
my guess, looking back on it.

00:04:24.830 --> 00:04:27.230 align:middle line:84%
But I remember
just kind of the--

00:04:27.230 --> 00:04:29.670 align:middle line:84%
there was a certain
Spartan quality to it,

00:04:29.670 --> 00:04:32.095 align:middle line:84%
but there was a
real beauty in that.

00:04:32.095 --> 00:04:33.470 align:middle line:84%
And then I was
seeing the mounds,

00:04:33.470 --> 00:04:36.403 align:middle line:84%
the burial mounds and such
that I had never seen before,

00:04:36.403 --> 00:04:38.570 align:middle line:84%
and was just having people
explain all of it and all

00:04:38.570 --> 00:04:41.000 align:middle line:84%
the scents of the
kimchi barrels,

00:04:41.000 --> 00:04:43.250 align:middle line:84%
once we were in
the towns and such,

00:04:43.250 --> 00:04:47.060 align:middle line:84%
and such a completely different
sensual experience compared

00:04:47.060 --> 00:04:49.670 align:middle line:84%
to living, growing up--
well, I'm from San Francisco

00:04:49.670 --> 00:04:50.720 align:middle line:90%
and Marin County--

00:04:50.720 --> 00:04:52.180 align:middle line:90%
very different, obviously.

00:04:52.180 --> 00:04:53.307 align:middle line:90%
>> OGLE: Yeah.

00:04:53.307 --> 00:04:55.140 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: Part of what
I'm getting at, too,

00:04:55.140 --> 00:04:57.640 align:middle line:84%
is the nature of life
because you were living more

00:04:57.640 --> 00:04:58.440 align:middle line:90%
their life.

00:04:58.440 --> 00:05:02.210 align:middle line:84%
It's not like you were moving
into an expat community

00:05:02.210 --> 00:05:04.040 align:middle line:84%
with a bunch of
Europeans and Americans

00:05:04.040 --> 00:05:05.960 align:middle line:84%
and the pace and the
way we do things.

00:05:05.960 --> 00:05:08.880 align:middle line:84%
You were moving in with the
pace of another group of people.

00:05:08.880 --> 00:05:09.680 align:middle line:90%
>> OGLE: Yeah.

00:05:09.680 --> 00:05:12.350 align:middle line:10%
My first five years, we
lived in a house that

00:05:12.350 --> 00:05:15.290 align:middle line:10%
was in a Korean
neighborhood and pretty much

00:05:15.290 --> 00:05:18.380 align:middle line:10%
a Korean-style
house for the time.

00:05:18.380 --> 00:05:21.920 align:middle line:84%
In later years, we moved
into a slightly bigger, more

00:05:21.920 --> 00:05:24.380 align:middle line:84%
kind of Western-style
house, but we were still

00:05:24.380 --> 00:05:27.840 align:middle line:84%
within the Korean community,
and that did make a difference.

00:05:27.840 --> 00:05:30.080 align:middle line:84%
I mean, looking back
on how I grew up

00:05:30.080 --> 00:05:33.020 align:middle line:84%
and comparing it to how
my kids grew up now,

00:05:33.020 --> 00:05:35.670 align:middle line:90%
it was a very different world.

00:05:35.670 --> 00:05:38.780 align:middle line:84%
And the time aspect that we've
brought up here, I think,

00:05:38.780 --> 00:05:40.010 align:middle line:90%
did make a difference.

00:05:40.010 --> 00:05:41.810 align:middle line:84%
But I think that
that's something that

00:05:41.810 --> 00:05:43.550 align:middle line:90%
is found all over the place.

00:05:43.550 --> 00:05:47.220 align:middle line:84%
50 years ago, life was slower
no matter where you were.

00:05:47.220 --> 00:05:48.530 align:middle line:90%
>> REGINA: Yes, indeed.

00:05:48.530 --> 00:05:50.540 align:middle line:84%
>> OGLE: And so it
was slower there,

00:05:50.540 --> 00:05:56.480 align:middle line:84%
and it was lived at a pace
that kind of, I think,

00:05:56.480 --> 00:06:00.830 align:middle line:84%
is more commensurate with
the human body and mind.

00:06:00.830 --> 00:06:05.390 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: And philosophically,
was the Korean understanding

00:06:05.390 --> 00:06:08.240 align:middle line:84%
that they were part of nature
and nature is part of us,

00:06:08.240 --> 00:06:09.530 align:middle line:90%
we're all one and the same?

00:06:09.530 --> 00:06:11.570 align:middle line:84%
That's abstract thinking
for a little kid.

00:06:11.570 --> 00:06:14.180 align:middle line:84%
Did any of that
feeling come up then?

00:06:14.180 --> 00:06:16.500 align:middle line:84%
Like here, the Native
American culture, for example,

00:06:16.500 --> 00:06:19.040 align:middle line:84%
is known for never
having disconnected

00:06:19.040 --> 00:06:22.200 align:middle line:84%
from Mother Earth,
Father Sky, and so forth.

00:06:22.200 --> 00:06:23.000 align:middle line:90%
Yeah.

00:06:23.000 --> 00:06:23.300 align:middle line:90%
>> OGLE: Yeah.

00:06:23.300 --> 00:06:25.508 align:middle line:84%
As a child, it would have
been a little bit abstract.

00:06:25.508 --> 00:06:27.660 align:middle line:84%
But what carried
through is that there

00:06:27.660 --> 00:06:30.350 align:middle line:84%
was a lot of different
religious traditions

00:06:30.350 --> 00:06:32.630 align:middle line:84%
that were already there,
and then Christianity

00:06:32.630 --> 00:06:34.860 align:middle line:84%
was being mixed into
that and so forth.

00:06:34.860 --> 00:06:39.200 align:middle line:84%
So you had Buddhism, and even
the ancient shamanism was still

00:06:39.200 --> 00:06:41.215 align:middle line:90%
present and Shintoism.

00:06:41.215 --> 00:06:44.730 align:middle line:84%
It was all there and I think
informed people's lives

00:06:44.730 --> 00:06:45.530 align:middle line:90%
in different ways.

00:06:45.530 --> 00:06:48.030 align:middle line:84%
I can't speak to it
in a scholarly way.

00:06:48.030 --> 00:06:50.840 align:middle line:84%
But looking back on it,
I feel like my resonance

00:06:50.840 --> 00:06:52.850 align:middle line:84%
with a lot of feelings
about, for instance,

00:06:52.850 --> 00:06:55.850 align:middle line:84%
this Gaia theory idea that
I'd been very much into--

00:06:55.850 --> 00:06:59.390 align:middle line:84%
I was very amenable to
that because just the way

00:06:59.390 --> 00:07:02.345 align:middle line:84%
I thought being steeped in
that culture and that language.

00:07:02.345 --> 00:07:05.570 align:middle line:84%
That's a hypothesis
that I have about why I

00:07:05.570 --> 00:07:07.490 align:middle line:90%
came to love this idea so much.

00:07:07.490 --> 00:07:09.530 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: And explain
what the idea is.

00:07:09.530 --> 00:07:11.037 align:middle line:90%
>> OGLE: The Gaia theory idea?

00:07:11.037 --> 00:07:11.870 align:middle line:90%
>> REGINA: Yes, yes.

00:07:11.870 --> 00:07:15.020 align:middle line:84%
>> OGLE: Well, so Gaia
theory, as a science,

00:07:15.020 --> 00:07:18.770 align:middle line:84%
is the scientific idea that
Earth is a single living

00:07:18.770 --> 00:07:20.280 align:middle line:90%
system.

00:07:20.280 --> 00:07:22.340 align:middle line:84%
And sometimes people
quibble about words,

00:07:22.340 --> 00:07:24.860 align:middle line:84%
like is it an organism
or a cell or whatever,

00:07:24.860 --> 00:07:27.470 align:middle line:84%
but I just feel like it's
a single living system.

00:07:27.470 --> 00:07:30.020 align:middle line:84%
And that's scientifically
verifiable.

00:07:30.020 --> 00:07:34.850 align:middle line:84%
It basically is our present
earth system science.

00:07:34.850 --> 00:07:37.430 align:middle line:84%
But the source of the
metaphor Gaia, I think,

00:07:37.430 --> 00:07:40.220 align:middle line:84%
ties into that science
and is an interesting part

00:07:40.220 --> 00:07:41.450 align:middle line:90%
of the history of it.

00:07:41.450 --> 00:07:43.670 align:middle line:90%
>> REGINA: Explain that, Gaia.

00:07:43.670 --> 00:07:46.100 align:middle line:10%
>> OGLE: The scientist who
came up with this idea,

00:07:46.100 --> 00:07:49.650 align:middle line:10%
his name is James
Lovelock, and he is a Brit.

00:07:49.650 --> 00:07:53.270 align:middle line:10%
And he was hired by
NASA back in the 1960s

00:07:53.270 --> 00:07:56.900 align:middle line:10%
to find out whether or not
there was life on Mars.

00:07:56.900 --> 00:07:59.797 align:middle line:10%
And he came and he worked
with folks like Carl Sagan,

00:07:59.797 --> 00:08:01.880 align:middle line:10%
and they said, how are we
going to determine this?

00:08:01.880 --> 00:08:04.710 align:middle line:10%
And at that time, you
couldn't go to Mars,

00:08:04.710 --> 00:08:08.120 align:middle line:10%
but you could measure the
atmosphere of other planets.

00:08:08.120 --> 00:08:09.500 align:middle line:10%
And so they did that.

00:08:09.500 --> 00:08:13.670 align:middle line:10%
And just based, basically, on
the composition of the Martian

00:08:13.670 --> 00:08:16.280 align:middle line:10%
atmosphere, he came
to the conclusion

00:08:16.280 --> 00:08:19.340 align:middle line:10%
that there was no life
on Mars because it

00:08:19.340 --> 00:08:22.880 align:middle line:10%
was a static atmosphere,
an atmosphere that might be

00:08:22.880 --> 00:08:25.280 align:middle line:10%
kind of like an EKG going flat.

00:08:25.280 --> 00:08:27.293 align:middle line:90%
Nothing's happening.

00:08:27.293 --> 00:08:29.460 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: At least nothing
detectable at that time.

00:08:29.460 --> 00:08:30.970 align:middle line:84%
>> OGLE: Detectable
at that time--

00:08:30.970 --> 00:08:31.550 align:middle line:90%
that's true.

00:08:31.550 --> 00:08:34.289 align:middle line:84%
But based on that, he told NASA
that he didn't think that there

00:08:34.289 --> 00:08:36.470 align:middle line:90%
was any life on Mars.

00:08:36.470 --> 00:08:40.020 align:middle line:84%
Having had a chance to talk with
him, he said that then at least

00:08:40.020 --> 00:08:42.770 align:middle line:84%
we proved that there
was life on Earth.

00:08:42.770 --> 00:08:44.270 align:middle line:84%
And he kind of
chuckles a little bit

00:08:44.270 --> 00:08:47.710 align:middle line:84%
because his point was that that
was his flash of insight where

00:08:47.710 --> 00:08:50.210 align:middle line:84%
you're saying, we weren't
really even testing

00:08:50.210 --> 00:08:52.730 align:middle line:84%
to see if there was
life on the planet.

00:08:52.730 --> 00:08:55.310 align:middle line:84%
We were testing to see
if the planet itself,

00:08:55.310 --> 00:08:58.650 align:middle line:84%
in some way, shape, or
form, was a living system.

00:08:58.650 --> 00:09:02.570 align:middle line:84%
And so he saw what is on Earth
and our atmospheric composition

00:09:02.570 --> 00:09:05.090 align:middle line:84%
and said that,
well, really, Earth

00:09:05.090 --> 00:09:08.070 align:middle line:84%
is a living system, the whole
thing, the rock, the water,

00:09:08.070 --> 00:09:09.870 align:middle line:90%
the air, the organisms.

00:09:09.870 --> 00:09:12.290 align:middle line:84%
And that's where his
Gaia hypothesis, then,

00:09:12.290 --> 00:09:15.157 align:middle line:84%
was born just out of
that simple insight.

00:09:15.157 --> 00:09:16.115 align:middle line:90%
>> REGINA: Interesting.

00:09:16.115 --> 00:09:17.150 align:middle line:90%
>> OGLE: Yea.

00:09:17.150 --> 00:09:19.850 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: Our ancestors knew
you couldn't separate from

00:09:19.850 --> 00:09:24.650 align:middle line:84%
the Earth, that they were part
of this living system of Gaia.

00:09:24.650 --> 00:09:29.150 align:middle line:84%
And so at what point
in our Western history

00:09:29.150 --> 00:09:33.020 align:middle line:84%
did we start removing ourselves
and considering ourselves

00:09:33.020 --> 00:09:37.298 align:middle line:84%
above the Earth which has
given birth to all of us?

00:09:37.298 --> 00:09:38.840 align:middle line:84%
>> OGLE: Well, that's
a big question,

00:09:38.840 --> 00:09:40.430 align:middle line:90%
and I'm not a scholar either.

00:09:40.430 --> 00:09:43.130 align:middle line:84%
But having really been
interested in, first,

00:09:43.130 --> 00:09:46.160 align:middle line:84%
the science, and then
how our culture views

00:09:46.160 --> 00:09:49.640 align:middle line:84%
that science, and
then the metaphor,

00:09:49.640 --> 00:09:51.060 align:middle line:90%
I have my ideas on it.

00:09:51.060 --> 00:09:55.010 align:middle line:84%
And I think it's where we
started to separate things

00:09:55.010 --> 00:09:57.350 align:middle line:90%
out even conceptually.

00:09:57.350 --> 00:10:01.310 align:middle line:84%
So the term "Gaia" is
from ancient Greece,

00:10:01.310 --> 00:10:04.340 align:middle line:84%
the ancient Greek
Goddess of Earth.

00:10:04.340 --> 00:10:09.320 align:middle line:10%
But shortly into, like, say,
the classical Greek period,

00:10:09.320 --> 00:10:12.350 align:middle line:10%
we had a time period where
we were separating out words

00:10:12.350 --> 00:10:16.820 align:middle line:10%
already so that, for instance,
"physis" was originally

00:10:16.820 --> 00:10:18.950 align:middle line:10%
the Greek word for nature.

00:10:18.950 --> 00:10:23.710 align:middle line:84%
And then there were separations
into "physis" became more

00:10:23.710 --> 00:10:28.600 align:middle line:84%
the physical world, and
"bios," which previously was

00:10:28.600 --> 00:10:32.680 align:middle line:84%
a way of life or the human
existence in the Earth,

00:10:32.680 --> 00:10:37.000 align:middle line:84%
became biology and separated out
into those kinds of thoughts.

00:10:37.000 --> 00:10:40.840 align:middle line:84%
And then later on in Europe,
we really ran with that.

00:10:40.840 --> 00:10:43.900 align:middle line:84%
We named entire disciplines--
geology, and biology,

00:10:43.900 --> 00:10:45.890 align:middle line:90%
and geometry, et cetera.

00:10:45.890 --> 00:10:48.520 align:middle line:84%
And so we began to
separate our thinking.

00:10:48.520 --> 00:10:50.590 align:middle line:84%
And then once our
thinking became separated,

00:10:50.590 --> 00:10:53.440 align:middle line:84%
we didn't have the
intuitive connection

00:10:53.440 --> 00:10:56.830 align:middle line:84%
to seeing that those used to
be just viscerally thought

00:10:56.830 --> 00:10:58.210 align:middle line:90%
as one and the same.

00:10:58.210 --> 00:11:01.210 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: And yet, in the
sort of mystical sense,

00:11:01.210 --> 00:11:04.642 align:middle line:84%
during the same ages,
it was understood.

00:11:04.642 --> 00:11:06.850 align:middle line:84%
Again, you have you scientists
of the day, of course,

00:11:06.850 --> 00:11:09.670 align:middle line:84%
who began parting it
out characteristically,

00:11:09.670 --> 00:11:12.310 align:middle line:84%
the features of what
Earth represented.

00:11:12.310 --> 00:11:14.410 align:middle line:84%
And then you still had
the mystical sects,

00:11:14.410 --> 00:11:17.200 align:middle line:84%
which carried forward more
ancient knowledge, which

00:11:17.200 --> 00:11:21.100 align:middle line:84%
actually considered the
Earth as an entity herself,

00:11:21.100 --> 00:11:24.460 align:middle line:84%
as among the other planets,
almost as having ruling

00:11:24.460 --> 00:11:27.820 align:middle line:84%
entities, archangels
that were giving

00:11:27.820 --> 00:11:30.860 align:middle line:84%
guidance to the development
of all these planets.

00:11:30.860 --> 00:11:33.400 align:middle line:84%
So it's interesting
because, at that time,

00:11:33.400 --> 00:11:35.680 align:middle line:84%
those philosophies
were not non-existence.

00:11:35.680 --> 00:11:37.480 align:middle line:84%
They were running
alongside, and they

00:11:37.480 --> 00:11:39.760 align:middle line:84%
were highly respected
among certain groups

00:11:39.760 --> 00:11:43.220 align:middle line:84%
of people and even the
masses, to a large extent.

00:11:43.220 --> 00:11:46.330 align:middle line:84%
So the masses still
believed that Mother Earth

00:11:46.330 --> 00:11:50.170 align:middle line:84%
is an entity that has
intelligence and gives

00:11:50.170 --> 00:11:51.160 align:middle line:90%
us guidance.

00:11:51.160 --> 00:11:52.600 align:middle line:84%
But somewhere
along the way, that

00:11:52.600 --> 00:11:54.590 align:middle line:90%
was squashed out completely.

00:11:54.590 --> 00:11:55.390 align:middle line:90%
Right?

00:11:55.390 --> 00:11:57.640 align:middle line:84%
>> OGLE: I think that what
you're describing happened,

00:11:57.640 --> 00:11:59.200 align:middle line:84%
but also that it
was a slow process,

00:11:59.200 --> 00:12:01.150 align:middle line:90%
that it didn't happen overnight.

00:12:01.150 --> 00:12:04.450 align:middle line:84%
And an example of that is
if you take a geology course

00:12:04.450 --> 00:12:07.750 align:middle line:84%
these days you find out
that Robert Hutton was

00:12:07.750 --> 00:12:09.040 align:middle line:90%
the father of geology.

00:12:09.040 --> 00:12:11.050 align:middle line:90%
This was back in the 1700s.

00:12:11.050 --> 00:12:13.540 align:middle line:84%
He was a medical
doctor by training,

00:12:13.540 --> 00:12:18.040 align:middle line:84%
and he came to see Earth
as having a physiology,

00:12:18.040 --> 00:12:20.920 align:middle line:84%
and he was interested
in the rocks and kind

00:12:20.920 --> 00:12:23.350 align:middle line:84%
of geologic principles
as understanding

00:12:23.350 --> 00:12:25.030 align:middle line:90%
the physiology of the planet.

00:12:25.030 --> 00:12:27.560 align:middle line:84%
He actually called
it a super organism.

00:12:27.560 --> 00:12:29.920 align:middle line:84%
So even at that point
in European history,

00:12:29.920 --> 00:12:32.590 align:middle line:84%
there was still a lot of
understanding and carryover

00:12:32.590 --> 00:12:35.140 align:middle line:84%
of kind of more ancient
views of things,

00:12:35.140 --> 00:12:39.160 align:middle line:84%
of Earth as being a mother
and our source of life.

00:12:39.160 --> 00:12:42.160 align:middle line:84%
But then, as time went on,
those separations continued,

00:12:42.160 --> 00:12:45.670 align:middle line:84%
and I dare say that most
geology students today

00:12:45.670 --> 00:12:47.710 align:middle line:84%
don't know that
"g" is from "Gaia"

00:12:47.710 --> 00:12:49.930 align:middle line:84%
and that Robert Hutton
was a medical doctor

00:12:49.930 --> 00:12:53.210 align:middle line:84%
and that he was interested
in Earth as a super organism.

00:12:53.210 --> 00:12:56.167 align:middle line:84%
So we slowly start to
separate over time.

00:12:56.167 --> 00:12:58.750 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: Well, and then with
that came what I consider to be

00:12:58.750 --> 00:13:03.100 align:middle line:84%
a type of arrogance in which,
as we developed our intellect,

00:13:03.100 --> 00:13:06.430 align:middle line:84%
especially as education became
more available to the masses

00:13:06.430 --> 00:13:09.500 align:middle line:84%
and such, as we began to
develop the intellect,

00:13:09.500 --> 00:13:12.730 align:middle line:84%
we started forgetting about
the notion of intelligence.

00:13:12.730 --> 00:13:15.910 align:middle line:84%
I think it's very
difficult to even conceive

00:13:15.910 --> 00:13:19.930 align:middle line:84%
of what could fashion something
like an Earth, no less

00:13:19.930 --> 00:13:21.940 align:middle line:90%
a rose blossom, you know?

00:13:21.940 --> 00:13:23.530 align:middle line:84%
What can fashion
something like that?

00:13:23.530 --> 00:13:28.480 align:middle line:84%
What kind of intelligence can
make for such complex systems

00:13:28.480 --> 00:13:30.590 align:middle line:90%
depending upon one another?

00:13:30.590 --> 00:13:33.950 align:middle line:84%
And again, this notion of
intellect versus intelligence--

00:13:33.950 --> 00:13:36.040 align:middle line:90%
natural intelligence.

00:13:36.040 --> 00:13:38.290 align:middle line:84%
Can you flow into
that a little bit?

00:13:38.290 --> 00:13:40.640 align:middle line:84%
>> OGLE: The word "arrogance"
is interesting to me, too,

00:13:40.640 --> 00:13:44.140 align:middle line:84%
because, especially these
days, I think everyone is kind

00:13:44.140 --> 00:13:47.810 align:middle line:84%
of at odds and loggerheads,
and we consider the other side

00:13:47.810 --> 00:13:48.610 align:middle line:90%
arrogant.

00:13:48.610 --> 00:13:52.317 align:middle line:84%
So I like to think more that we
really think that we're right.

00:13:52.317 --> 00:13:53.650 align:middle line:90%
>> REGINA: We think we're right.

00:13:53.650 --> 00:13:54.450 align:middle line:90%
>> OGLE: Yeah.

00:13:54.450 --> 00:13:58.150 align:middle line:84%
And it's based on our
experience and our knowledge

00:13:58.150 --> 00:13:59.410 align:middle line:90%
and everything about us.

00:13:59.410 --> 00:14:02.920 align:middle line:84%
And so we end up entrenching
into different sides,

00:14:02.920 --> 00:14:05.560 align:middle line:84%
I think, a little bit
too easily these days.

00:14:05.560 --> 00:14:07.870 align:middle line:84%
But what I'm
interested in is maybe

00:14:07.870 --> 00:14:10.810 align:middle line:84%
finding out if we can
talk to each other

00:14:10.810 --> 00:14:14.470 align:middle line:84%
about each other's
intelligences and intellect

00:14:14.470 --> 00:14:18.040 align:middle line:84%
in order to figure out
the best understanding.

00:14:18.040 --> 00:14:22.850 align:middle line:84%
So for instance, even this
idea of how Earth came to be,

00:14:22.850 --> 00:14:26.030 align:middle line:84%
that's going to be probably
forever swathed the mystery.

00:14:26.030 --> 00:14:26.830 align:middle line:90%
>> REGINA: Right.

00:14:26.830 --> 00:14:28.635 align:middle line:84%
I mean, and that's
a question that's--

00:14:28.635 --> 00:14:31.200 align:middle line:84%
it's a valid question that
needs to be talked about.

00:14:31.200 --> 00:14:32.050 align:middle line:90%
>> OGLE: Right.

00:14:32.050 --> 00:14:34.970 align:middle line:84%
And there is a lot of scientific
understanding of that,

00:14:34.970 --> 00:14:37.425 align:middle line:84%
but that still goes back
to ultimate realities

00:14:37.425 --> 00:14:38.800 align:middle line:84%
that I don't know
that we'll ever

00:14:38.800 --> 00:14:41.260 align:middle line:84%
be able to solve
even scientifically.

00:14:41.260 --> 00:14:44.690 align:middle line:84%
But the thing about
language growing up--

00:14:44.690 --> 00:14:46.330 align:middle line:84%
one of the reasons
why I came to think

00:14:46.330 --> 00:14:48.730 align:middle line:84%
that I did resonate
with the Gaia theory

00:14:48.730 --> 00:14:54.730 align:middle line:84%
is that the Gaia theory
implies that there's systems

00:14:54.730 --> 00:14:59.380 align:middle line:84%
and balance can emerge with
no forethought, just out

00:14:59.380 --> 00:15:03.800 align:middle line:84%
of its own accord, just out
of the natural way of things.

00:15:03.800 --> 00:15:10.300 align:middle line:84%
And when I found out as an adult
that the character for nature

00:15:10.300 --> 00:15:13.510 align:middle line:84%
that's often used in the Orient,
stemming from the Chinese,

00:15:13.510 --> 00:15:18.460 align:middle line:84%
is two characters, "of
itself so, of itself so,"

00:15:18.460 --> 00:15:22.360 align:middle line:84%
and it's the same word that's
often used for "spontaneous--"

00:15:22.360 --> 00:15:25.240 align:middle line:84%
in other words, there's
no need to conceive

00:15:25.240 --> 00:15:29.560 align:middle line:84%
a committee or a single
power, although that

00:15:29.560 --> 00:15:32.870 align:middle line:90%
could be creating the Earth.

00:15:32.870 --> 00:15:37.840 align:middle line:84%
You get a order and a balance
and a harmony that arises out

00:15:37.840 --> 00:15:40.240 align:middle line:90%
of a system, of itself so.

00:15:40.240 --> 00:15:42.940 align:middle line:84%
And so if we were to talk
to each other in those ways,

00:15:42.940 --> 00:15:44.860 align:middle line:84%
maybe we'd find
out that we kind of

00:15:44.860 --> 00:15:48.190 align:middle line:84%
feel the same, even though
we're using different language.

00:15:48.190 --> 00:15:51.220 align:middle line:84%
More and more of that might
lead to better understanding

00:15:51.220 --> 00:15:54.920 align:middle line:84%
and agreement between people
rather than loggerheads.

00:15:54.920 --> 00:15:55.720 align:middle line:90%
>> REGINA: Right.

00:15:55.720 --> 00:15:57.512 align:middle line:84%
But then we have to
assume we don't already

00:15:57.512 --> 00:15:58.840 align:middle line:90%
know all the answers.

00:15:58.840 --> 00:16:00.140 align:middle line:90%
>> OGLE: Yes, absolutely.

00:16:00.140 --> 00:16:01.450 align:middle line:90%
>> REGINA: That's a problem.

00:16:01.450 --> 00:16:02.645 align:middle line:90%
That's a problem that can--

00:16:02.645 --> 00:16:04.270 align:middle line:84%
it's not a problem
that can't be fixed,

00:16:04.270 --> 00:16:05.690 align:middle line:84%
but it's a problem
at the moment,

00:16:05.690 --> 00:16:08.680 align:middle line:84%
especially as we look
at how polarized society

00:16:08.680 --> 00:16:09.820 align:middle line:90%
and viewpoints have become.

00:16:09.820 --> 00:16:12.360 align:middle line:84%
But then let's extend
that notion out to nature.

00:16:12.360 --> 00:16:14.890 align:middle line:84%
Everything is
based on opposites.

00:16:14.890 --> 00:16:18.610 align:middle line:84%
Everything is based on the
need for the poles to interact.

00:16:18.610 --> 00:16:21.790 align:middle line:84%
There's polarity in everything,
positive and negative, right?

00:16:21.790 --> 00:16:26.110 align:middle line:84%
And so that's essential just for
creation itself on all levels.

00:16:26.110 --> 00:16:28.990 align:middle line:84%
And yet, at the same time,
the Earth and all systems

00:16:28.990 --> 00:16:32.840 align:middle line:84%
are naturally
seeking homeostasis.

00:16:32.840 --> 00:16:36.520 align:middle line:84%
So to me, it's a really
interesting prospect

00:16:36.520 --> 00:16:38.788 align:middle line:84%
that humanity-- if we can
kind of go along that line

00:16:38.788 --> 00:16:40.330 align:middle line:84%
that you're talking
about and finding

00:16:40.330 --> 00:16:43.300 align:middle line:84%
that way culturally and
socially between us,

00:16:43.300 --> 00:16:45.190 align:middle line:84%
it's like there is a
point to the polarity

00:16:45.190 --> 00:16:48.490 align:middle line:84%
because it does bring
different knowledge bases

00:16:48.490 --> 00:16:51.190 align:middle line:84%
and such into the
equation, but ultimately it

00:16:51.190 --> 00:16:53.570 align:middle line:90%
has to result in homeostasis.

00:16:53.570 --> 00:16:56.080 align:middle line:84%
And homeostasis
isn't exactly what

00:16:56.080 --> 00:16:57.980 align:middle line:90%
society's aiming at right now.

00:16:57.980 --> 00:16:58.780 align:middle line:90%
>> OGLE: Yeah.

00:16:58.780 --> 00:17:01.870 align:middle line:84%
Homeostasis, of
course, is one thing

00:17:01.870 --> 00:17:04.569 align:middle line:84%
that scientists have had a
little problem with in terms

00:17:04.569 --> 00:17:07.060 align:middle line:84%
of the Gaia theory because
they say, oh, Earth

00:17:07.060 --> 00:17:08.837 align:middle line:90%
has never had a homeostasis.

00:17:08.837 --> 00:17:10.420 align:middle line:84%
In other words,
conditions have always

00:17:10.420 --> 00:17:13.040 align:middle line:84%
changed through vast
periods of time.

00:17:13.040 --> 00:17:16.525 align:middle line:84%
But what is true is there's
been vast periods of homeostasis

00:17:16.525 --> 00:17:17.349 align:middle line:90%
within that.

00:17:17.349 --> 00:17:18.349 align:middle line:90%
>> REGINA: Yes, exactly.

00:17:18.349 --> 00:17:21.730 align:middle line:84%
>> OGLE: So for instance, so we
have 21% oxygen and it's proved

00:17:21.730 --> 00:17:25.300 align:middle line:84%
that that's probably been that
case for about 200 million

00:17:25.300 --> 00:17:27.470 align:middle line:84%
years, a nice healthy
chunk of time.

00:17:27.470 --> 00:17:29.980 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: Right, enough
to allow life to flourish.

00:17:29.980 --> 00:17:33.310 align:middle line:84%
>> OGLE: Life as we know it
today because life before

00:17:33.310 --> 00:17:34.690 align:middle line:90%
flourished in a different--

00:17:34.690 --> 00:17:35.000 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: In a
different way-- yeah.

00:17:35.000 --> 00:17:36.250 align:middle line:84%
>> OGLE: --world
in a different way.

00:17:36.250 --> 00:17:37.458 align:middle line:90%
>> REGINA: Different species.

00:17:37.458 --> 00:17:39.910 align:middle line:84%
>> OGLE: And so for
us as human beings,

00:17:39.910 --> 00:17:44.650 align:middle line:84%
I guess my concern is that
we don't change that existing

00:17:44.650 --> 00:17:49.930 align:middle line:84%
homeostasis too much such that
it would become harmful for us

00:17:49.930 --> 00:17:52.530 align:middle line:90%
and our immediate descendants.

00:17:52.530 --> 00:17:54.790 align:middle line:84%
It will change eventually,
and we may or may not

00:17:54.790 --> 00:17:56.230 align:middle line:90%
be a part of the mix.

00:17:56.230 --> 00:17:57.700 align:middle line:84%
But right now,
it'd be good if we

00:17:57.700 --> 00:18:00.580 align:middle line:84%
could have our grandkids
live in a world that's

00:18:00.580 --> 00:18:01.810 align:middle line:90%
somewhat the same as ours.

00:18:01.810 --> 00:18:03.685 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: Well, this
is part of the problem.

00:18:03.685 --> 00:18:05.620 align:middle line:84%
We are part of that
mix of the change.

00:18:05.620 --> 00:18:07.630 align:middle line:84%
Let's just talk about
some of the challenges

00:18:07.630 --> 00:18:10.720 align:middle line:84%
because these aren't things
that are unknown to the viewers,

00:18:10.720 --> 00:18:14.020 align:middle line:84%
but what the implications of
this mean in the long term.

00:18:14.020 --> 00:18:16.960 align:middle line:84%
For example, the oxygen
rates of this planet

00:18:16.960 --> 00:18:19.630 align:middle line:84%
as a result of
deforestation alone,

00:18:19.630 --> 00:18:21.377 align:middle line:90%
what's happening with this?

00:18:21.377 --> 00:18:23.710 align:middle line:84%
>> OGLE: Well, I think the
oxygen rates themselves right

00:18:23.710 --> 00:18:27.820 align:middle line:84%
now are still
pretty close to 21%.

00:18:27.820 --> 00:18:30.190 align:middle line:84%
In fact, you couldn't
have large vertebrates

00:18:30.190 --> 00:18:33.033 align:middle line:90%
of any kind living at 17%.

00:18:33.033 --> 00:18:34.450 align:middle line:84%
So that's one of
the clues that we

00:18:34.450 --> 00:18:37.630 align:middle line:84%
have that it's never dropped
below that over, say, 200

00:18:37.630 --> 00:18:38.430 align:middle line:90%
million years.

00:18:38.430 --> 00:18:39.100 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: Well,
that's good news.

00:18:39.100 --> 00:18:40.433 align:middle line:90%
>> OGLE: Yeah, that's good news.

00:18:40.433 --> 00:18:42.310 align:middle line:84%
But other things,
notably carbon dioxide,

00:18:42.310 --> 00:18:47.380 align:middle line:84%
are going in slight but
very significant directions,

00:18:47.380 --> 00:18:49.210 align:middle line:90%
and that's just a fact.

00:18:49.210 --> 00:18:52.390 align:middle line:84%
And its impact on
climate, for instance,

00:18:52.390 --> 00:18:56.110 align:middle line:84%
that's already happened is
also factual and verifiable.

00:18:56.110 --> 00:18:59.950 align:middle line:84%
The impact into the future, we
can argue about it all we want,

00:18:59.950 --> 00:19:01.900 align:middle line:84%
but the scientific
read right now

00:19:01.900 --> 00:19:06.748 align:middle line:84%
is that it's headed in really
dangerous ways for humanity.

00:19:06.748 --> 00:19:09.040 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: Because we're
talking about the environment,

00:19:09.040 --> 00:19:11.740 align:middle line:84%
we're talking about becoming
responsible grown ups

00:19:11.740 --> 00:19:14.890 align:middle line:84%
and working within
this living system,

00:19:14.890 --> 00:19:18.820 align:middle line:84%
as part of this living system,
it's certainly fair to point

00:19:18.820 --> 00:19:21.000 align:middle line:84%
out where we've been
living outside of that.

00:19:21.000 --> 00:19:23.383 align:middle line:84%
And a lot of that has to do
with what I call ignorance

00:19:23.383 --> 00:19:26.050 align:middle line:84%
in the truest sense of the word,
which is not that we don't have

00:19:26.050 --> 00:19:29.390 align:middle line:84%
knowledge, that we choose to
ignore it, for the most part,

00:19:29.390 --> 00:19:32.000 align:middle line:84%
which is what ignorance
is, is to ignore.

00:19:32.000 --> 00:19:34.690 align:middle line:84%
And so if we choose to
live in this ignorance,

00:19:34.690 --> 00:19:36.670 align:middle line:84%
obviously what you're
just talking about,

00:19:36.670 --> 00:19:38.650 align:middle line:84%
we're headed down
a particular path.

00:19:38.650 --> 00:19:41.680 align:middle line:84%
But then, again, you look at
some of the-- one little bit

00:19:41.680 --> 00:19:45.520 align:middle line:84%
I've been on recently is the
notion of just the one out

00:19:45.520 --> 00:19:47.590 align:middle line:84%
of thousands and thousands
of problems, which

00:19:47.590 --> 00:19:51.040 align:middle line:84%
is what's dropping on us
from the sky, heavy aluminum

00:19:51.040 --> 00:19:55.810 align:middle line:84%
loads from jet fuel and also
chemtrails and contrails alike,

00:19:55.810 --> 00:19:58.690 align:middle line:84%
and just what this
one thing does to all

00:19:58.690 --> 00:20:00.620 align:middle line:90%
the species on the planet.

00:20:00.620 --> 00:20:03.850 align:middle line:84%
And yet, when it comes to the
subject of climate change--

00:20:03.850 --> 00:20:07.180 align:middle line:84%
these things actually change
climate, literally move weather

00:20:07.180 --> 00:20:08.500 align:middle line:90%
fronts and so forth--

00:20:08.500 --> 00:20:10.930 align:middle line:90%
the subject never even comes up.

00:20:10.930 --> 00:20:13.480 align:middle line:84%
How can you even begin a
discourse on climate change

00:20:13.480 --> 00:20:16.780 align:middle line:84%
when you're changing the
climate literally in the sky

00:20:16.780 --> 00:20:17.935 align:middle line:90%
and not acknowledging it?

00:20:17.935 --> 00:20:20.310 align:middle line:84%
>> OGLE: Well, I guess one
read on that is that there are

00:20:20.310 --> 00:20:23.380 align:middle line:84%
so many-- you bring up aluminum,
and there's so many other ways,

00:20:23.380 --> 00:20:25.940 align:middle line:84%
whether it be CO2 or
aluminum or whatever else,

00:20:25.940 --> 00:20:28.090 align:middle line:90%
that are concurrently happening.

00:20:28.090 --> 00:20:30.420 align:middle line:84%
Therefore, it's almost
impossible for any one person

00:20:30.420 --> 00:20:34.260 align:middle line:84%
to be totally aware of all the
different things happening.

00:20:34.260 --> 00:20:38.040 align:middle line:84%
But it seems to me like
the single unifying factor

00:20:38.040 --> 00:20:42.640 align:middle line:84%
is that we continue to produce
more and more new things

00:20:42.640 --> 00:20:45.580 align:middle line:84%
and more and more stuff and
use it and put it into the air

00:20:45.580 --> 00:20:46.730 align:middle line:90%
kind of haphazardly.

00:20:46.730 --> 00:20:50.370 align:middle line:84%
And so scientifically,
we're kind

00:20:50.370 --> 00:20:53.670 align:middle line:84%
of approaching our lives
in a sloppy manner,

00:20:53.670 --> 00:20:56.520 align:middle line:84%
and we're making things
bad for ourselves

00:20:56.520 --> 00:20:58.300 align:middle line:90%
and for future generations.

00:20:58.300 --> 00:20:59.100 align:middle line:90%
>> REGINA: OK.

00:20:59.100 --> 00:21:01.590 align:middle line:84%
So now let's go back to
one of the simplest things.

00:21:01.590 --> 00:21:03.420 align:middle line:84%
And this is what I
was really intrigued

00:21:03.420 --> 00:21:06.930 align:middle line:84%
with about your work is we're
looking at some of what we're

00:21:06.930 --> 00:21:10.830 align:middle line:84%
doing on more of a technological
and substantive level and just

00:21:10.830 --> 00:21:13.080 align:middle line:90%
material level to planet Earth.

00:21:13.080 --> 00:21:14.310 align:middle line:90%
We know we have problems.

00:21:14.310 --> 00:21:16.020 align:middle line:84%
We know we have to
find our way out.

00:21:16.020 --> 00:21:21.630 align:middle line:84%
Honestly, I don't understand
how that's going to happen.

00:21:21.630 --> 00:21:23.352 align:middle line:84%
It's almost like
the human species

00:21:23.352 --> 00:21:24.810 align:middle line:84%
and the Earth is
just going to have

00:21:24.810 --> 00:21:28.650 align:middle line:84%
to adapt to this reality
we've created because who's

00:21:28.650 --> 00:21:30.090 align:middle line:90%
going to change it, really?

00:21:30.090 --> 00:21:32.670 align:middle line:84%
I mean, we can change
certain policies, absolutely.

00:21:32.670 --> 00:21:34.350 align:middle line:84%
We can certainly
change where it has

00:21:34.350 --> 00:21:37.463 align:middle line:84%
to do with some of
the kind of toxins

00:21:37.463 --> 00:21:39.630 align:middle line:84%
we talked about a moment
ago, but not the huge load.

00:21:39.630 --> 00:21:41.070 align:middle line:90%
Just take a flight alone.

00:21:41.070 --> 00:21:42.540 align:middle line:90%
Who's going to stop flying?

00:21:42.540 --> 00:21:45.540 align:middle line:84%
Who's going to stop these
industries from happening?

00:21:45.540 --> 00:21:49.110 align:middle line:84%
Who's going to stop that
load on the environment?

00:21:49.110 --> 00:21:52.110 align:middle line:84%
Nobody's willing to
give up the perks

00:21:52.110 --> 00:21:55.680 align:middle line:84%
that they've come to
appreciate of modern life

00:21:55.680 --> 00:21:57.060 align:middle line:90%
to a significant extent.

00:21:57.060 --> 00:22:01.630 align:middle line:84%
So if that's the case,
let's take the conversation

00:22:01.630 --> 00:22:02.430 align:middle line:90%
beyond that.

00:22:02.430 --> 00:22:04.350 align:middle line:90%
Earth does adapt.

00:22:04.350 --> 00:22:07.200 align:middle line:84%
Earth is going to be here
long after we're gone.

00:22:07.200 --> 00:22:09.870 align:middle line:84%
Species are going
to become extinct.

00:22:09.870 --> 00:22:11.970 align:middle line:84%
Other species will
be able to thrive

00:22:11.970 --> 00:22:14.790 align:middle line:84%
in whatever the new
environment is, I suppose.

00:22:14.790 --> 00:22:17.220 align:middle line:84%
And we can just look at
it as our species may

00:22:17.220 --> 00:22:20.070 align:middle line:84%
be one of those that just
isn't able to really adapt

00:22:20.070 --> 00:22:23.730 align:middle line:84%
quickly enough or maybe we
will be super fast adapters.

00:22:23.730 --> 00:22:25.830 align:middle line:90%
I don't know what that is.

00:22:25.830 --> 00:22:29.220 align:middle line:84%
But one thing we can get back
to is this notion of mind.

00:22:29.220 --> 00:22:31.860 align:middle line:84%
Obviously, Gaia has
an incredibly complex

00:22:31.860 --> 00:22:33.240 align:middle line:90%
intelligence.

00:22:33.240 --> 00:22:37.110 align:middle line:84%
And I've also read, in
other books and such,

00:22:37.110 --> 00:22:42.360 align:middle line:84%
even it's her, its own
emotions and so forth.

00:22:42.360 --> 00:22:44.460 align:middle line:84%
It's a complex,
multidimensional being

00:22:44.460 --> 00:22:47.220 align:middle line:84%
just as we're complex,
multidimensional beings.

00:22:47.220 --> 00:22:52.560 align:middle line:84%
So how do our minds and
our emotions work together?

00:22:52.560 --> 00:22:55.320 align:middle line:84%
>> OGLE: That's a really
interesting question.

00:22:55.320 --> 00:23:00.750 align:middle line:84%
And one thing I like to
think of is that we ourselves

00:23:00.750 --> 00:23:05.400 align:middle line:84%
are just seamlessly
interconnected with Gaia,

00:23:05.400 --> 00:23:11.380 align:middle line:84%
with life, with our world
such that we grew out of her.

00:23:11.380 --> 00:23:15.210 align:middle line:84%
And therefore, everything about
us did, including our minds,

00:23:15.210 --> 00:23:17.130 align:middle line:90%
including the ways we think.

00:23:17.130 --> 00:23:19.590 align:middle line:84%
And so I used to think
in a metaphoric sense,

00:23:19.590 --> 00:23:22.470 align:middle line:84%
but now I think, really,
in a literal sense.

00:23:22.470 --> 00:23:25.740 align:middle line:84%
When we as human beings acquired
all the different skills

00:23:25.740 --> 00:23:30.580 align:middle line:84%
that we have and abilities
and we invented a camera,

00:23:30.580 --> 00:23:33.300 align:middle line:84%
and then we invented
a spacecraft

00:23:33.300 --> 00:23:37.260 align:middle line:84%
and went out to outer space
and took a picture back,

00:23:37.260 --> 00:23:42.227 align:middle line:84%
that that was quite literally
Earth becoming self-conscious.

00:23:42.227 --> 00:23:44.310 align:middle line:84%
It's kind of an interesting
thing to think of it--

00:23:44.310 --> 00:23:44.820 align:middle line:90%
>> REGINA: That's interesting.

00:23:44.820 --> 00:23:47.280 align:middle line:84%
>> OGLE: --as literally,
not just metaphoric,

00:23:47.280 --> 00:23:50.280 align:middle line:84%
because if we did evolve out
of this planet and our minds

00:23:50.280 --> 00:23:52.530 align:middle line:84%
and everything about us did
evolve out of this planet,

00:23:52.530 --> 00:23:55.260 align:middle line:84%
then that's quite
literally what it is.

00:23:55.260 --> 00:23:59.010 align:middle line:84%
And if we start to think in
that way, at least to me,

00:23:59.010 --> 00:24:03.630 align:middle line:84%
it gives us a new view,
perhaps an optimistic view,

00:24:03.630 --> 00:24:08.610 align:middle line:84%
that we could evolve fast
enough to do things differently

00:24:08.610 --> 00:24:11.100 align:middle line:84%
in the short term, short
term meaning let's get

00:24:11.100 --> 00:24:15.630 align:middle line:84%
our policy and our actions and
everything fixed in short order

00:24:15.630 --> 00:24:19.290 align:middle line:84%
so that our kids and
grandkids have a good life

00:24:19.290 --> 00:24:21.460 align:middle line:90%
to expect into the future.

00:24:21.460 --> 00:24:23.490 align:middle line:84%
And one of the
practical ways in which

00:24:23.490 --> 00:24:25.530 align:middle line:84%
I've been interested
about that is just,

00:24:25.530 --> 00:24:29.820 align:middle line:84%
what would it take for us
to imagine and then create

00:24:29.820 --> 00:24:32.070 align:middle line:84%
a truly green
economy, as they say,

00:24:32.070 --> 00:24:35.580 align:middle line:84%
not a green-washed economy,
but a green economy in which we

00:24:35.580 --> 00:24:39.090 align:middle line:84%
really did things differently,
fundamentally differently,

00:24:39.090 --> 00:24:43.300 align:middle line:84%
so that we could live more in
homeostasis with the systems

00:24:43.300 --> 00:24:44.100 align:middle line:90%
around us?

00:24:44.100 --> 00:24:45.190 align:middle line:90%
And I think it's possible.

00:24:45.190 --> 00:24:46.440 align:middle line:90%
>> REGINA: I think it is, too.

00:24:46.440 --> 00:24:48.330 align:middle line:84%
And in fact, I love
that topic, so I

00:24:48.330 --> 00:24:51.090 align:middle line:84%
would like you to share that,
your thoughts on that with us

00:24:51.090 --> 00:24:57.360 align:middle line:84%
and your idea of what these--
and I know this isn't your job

00:24:57.360 --> 00:25:00.600 align:middle line:84%
to create these systems,
but just your vision of what

00:25:00.600 --> 00:25:02.877 align:middle line:84%
these systems could look
like so people can get

00:25:02.877 --> 00:25:04.710 align:middle line:84%
an idea in their own
minds is how they could

00:25:04.710 --> 00:25:08.490 align:middle line:84%
begin to even think this way and
start contributing in this way.

00:25:08.490 --> 00:25:12.450 align:middle line:84%
>> OGLE: Well, first would be at
least an awareness that things

00:25:12.450 --> 00:25:15.670 align:middle line:84%
don't always have to be
the way they are now.

00:25:15.670 --> 00:25:18.180 align:middle line:84%
So it's not just our
human nature necessarily

00:25:18.180 --> 00:25:20.940 align:middle line:84%
just to go consuming
ourselves to death

00:25:20.940 --> 00:25:23.220 align:middle line:84%
and hurrying ourselves
to death and plunging off

00:25:23.220 --> 00:25:26.770 align:middle line:84%
into the darkness
with those behaviors,

00:25:26.770 --> 00:25:30.150 align:middle line:84%
that people have lived
differently in the past

00:25:30.150 --> 00:25:32.490 align:middle line:84%
and have envisioned
different ways of living now.

00:25:32.490 --> 00:25:34.200 align:middle line:84%
There's entire groups
of people that have

00:25:34.200 --> 00:25:36.728 align:middle line:90%
chosen to live differently now.

00:25:36.728 --> 00:25:38.520 align:middle line:84%
So at least that's a
starting point where--

00:25:38.520 --> 00:25:41.062 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: Give us some examples
of what you think are really

00:25:41.062 --> 00:25:42.030 align:middle line:90%
good models for this.

00:25:42.030 --> 00:25:45.900 align:middle line:84%
>> OGLE: Well, even if you
just take between Europe

00:25:45.900 --> 00:25:50.490 align:middle line:84%
