00:26:07.530 --> 00:26:08.700 align:middle line:90%
than our own.

00:26:08.700 --> 00:26:10.890 align:middle line:90%
So there's one model.

00:26:10.890 --> 00:26:13.710 align:middle line:84%
Then you could go to any
number of other countries

00:26:13.710 --> 00:26:17.970 align:middle line:84%
around the world where they
use vastly less resources.

00:26:17.970 --> 00:26:19.830 align:middle line:84%
And yes, they have
their own challenges

00:26:19.830 --> 00:26:22.240 align:middle line:84%
of health and
pollution and so forth,

00:26:22.240 --> 00:26:25.180 align:middle line:84%
but maybe that's
because they're immersed

00:26:25.180 --> 00:26:27.400 align:middle line:84%
in kind of the first
world at the same time.

00:26:27.400 --> 00:26:28.450 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: They're trying to
play catch-up on the material

00:26:28.450 --> 00:26:29.250 align:middle line:90%
plane.

00:26:29.250 --> 00:26:31.090 align:middle line:84%
>> OGLE: They're
playing catch-up.

00:26:31.090 --> 00:26:34.230 align:middle line:84%
